+# Priorities Requirements Checklist: UC-27 Set Constraint Priorities
+
+**Purpose**: Validate the quality, clarity, and completeness of the constraint-priority requirements before implementation and review
+**Created**: 2026-03-11
+**Feature**: [spec.md](/home/thaia/ECE493Group19/specs/027-branch-constraint-priorities/spec.md)
+
+**Note**: This checklist is generated by the `/speckit.checklist` command based on feature context and requirements.
+
+## Requirement Completeness
+
+- [ ] CHK001 Are the eligible constraints for priority assignment explicitly defined, including whether all saved constraint types can be prioritized? [Completeness, Spec §FR-001, Spec §FR-010]
+- [ ] CHK002 Are the requirements explicit about whether every eligible constraint must receive a priority or whether documented defaults are permitted for unranked constraints? [Clarity, Spec §Edge Cases, Spec §FR-002]
+- [ ] CHK003 Are the save and replace semantics for the full priority set fully defined for create, update, and re-save scenarios? [Completeness, Spec §User Story 1, Spec §FR-004]
+- [ ] CHK004 Are the requirements complete for what happens to saved priorities when their referenced constraints are deleted, hidden, or otherwise unavailable? [Completeness, Spec §Edge Cases, Spec §FR-012]
+
+## Requirement Clarity
+
+- [ ] CHK005 Is the 1-to-5 scale defined unambiguously, including whether lower numbers always mean higher priority in every ranking context? [Clarity, Spec §Clarifications, Spec §FR-002]
+- [ ] CHK006 Is "displayed constraint order" precise enough to determine which order governs tie-breaking after sorting, filtering, or editing the editor view? [Ambiguity, Spec §FR-008, Spec §Tie-Breaking Rule]
+- [ ] CHK007 Is "outside the selected term" defined clearly enough to distinguish wrong-term references from deleted or stale constraints? [Clarity, Spec §FR-005, Spec §FR-012]
+- [ ] CHK008 Is "visible explanation" specific enough to evaluate message quality consistently across invalid-value and save-failure scenarios? [Measurability, Spec §NFR-002, Spec §SC-002]
+
+## Requirement Consistency
+
+- [ ] CHK009 Are the priority-model requirements consistent between the clarification note, user stories, functional requirements, assumptions, and key entities? [Consistency, Spec §Clarifications, Spec §FR-002, Spec §Assumptions, Spec §Key Entities]
+- [ ] CHK010 Are tie-handling requirements consistent between User Story 3, the edge-case section, FR-008, and SC-003? [Consistency, Spec §User Story 3, Spec §Edge Cases, Spec §FR-008, Spec §SC-003]
+- [ ] CHK011 Do the save-failure requirements align across User Story 3, FR-009, NFR-001, and SC-004 without implying contradictory partial-save behavior? [Consistency, Spec §User Story 3, Spec §FR-009, Spec §SC-004]
+
+## Acceptance Criteria Quality
+
+- [ ] CHK012 Are the success criteria measurable without depending on hidden implementation details about the ranking engine? [Acceptance Criteria, Spec §SC-001, Spec §SC-003]
+- [ ] CHK013 Can reviewers objectively determine what qualifies as "used during later schedule ranking" from the written requirements alone? [Measurability, Spec §User Story 1, Spec §FR-007, Spec §SC-001]
+- [ ] CHK014 Is the repeatability requirement for equal-priority ranking outcomes measurable enough to distinguish stable tie-breaking from accidental consistency? [Clarity, Spec §SC-003]
+
+## Scenario Coverage
